            <scopecontent id="aspace_b6c724012d2a78845d3b5266f51ae2fa">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The series contains various documents and ephemera, dating from 1899 to 1946, pertaining to commerce in Alaska and the Yukon Territory. The series is comprised of certificates, customs documents, bills, and receipts, which provide insight into daily life in the gold rush period (particularly in Skagway). The export and royalty certificates, in particular, chronicle the gold trade and its participants.</p>
            </scopecontent>
